- You would probably want to have a read of [Date And Time Functions](https://www.sqlite.org/lang_datefunc.html) e.g. for **strftime**, **julianday** and **now**
- rowid is a special normally hidden column that exists for all table unless it is WITHOUT ROWID table. It wouldn&#39;t typically be used, or if so aliased by using INTEGER PRIMARY KEY
  - see [SQLite Autoincrement](https://sqlite.org/autoinc.html) to find out about **rowid** and alias thereof and why not to use AUTOINCREMENT.
- a column type of **typedoesnotmatterthtamuch** see [Datatypes In SQLite Version 3](https://www.sqlite.org/datatype3.html) as to why this can be.


